From: BORE CFS Upgrade v5 for Kernel 6.1
Subject: [PATCH] sched: BORE upgrade - futex boost, hub/stub inheritance, burst preempt

Upgrades existing inline CFS BORE (~v3.1.4) to v5 with:
- sched_burst_inherit_type (0=none, 1=parent, 2=hub/stub) replaces fork_atavistic
- Unified sched_burst_smoothness (0-3) replaces long+short pair
- Futex waiting boost for lower mutex latency
- Thread group burst inheritance (CLONE_THREAD)
- Burst preemption via sched_bore & 2
- PREEMPT_SHORT_BORE feature for interactive task preemption
- Optimized defaults: offset=24, scale=1536, cache=75M

Default values updated:
  sched_bore = 1             (bit 0: BORE, bit 1: burst_preempt off by default)
  sched_burst_inherit_type = 2  (hub/stub ancestor)
  sched_burst_smoothness = 1    (mild EMA, was long=1 short=0)
  sched_burst_penalty_offset = 24 (was 22)
  sched_burst_penalty_scale = 1536 (was 1280)
  sched_burst_cache_lifetime = 75000000 (was 60000000)
  sched_burst_exclude_kthreads = 1 (unchanged)

Signed-off-by: BORE Upgrade Patch
